<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ871106-0051 </DOCNO><HL> Business Brief:Bausch andamp; Lomb Inc.</HL><DD> 11/06/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> BOL CAMBYTENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM) </IN><TEXT>   Bausch andamp; Lomb Inc. said it agreed to sell certain optical instruments businesses to Cambridge Instrument PLC for $37 million.    Bausch andamp; Lomb, a maker of eye care products based in Rochester, N.Y., said the agreement to sell its microscope, photogrammetry and diagnostic ophthalmic instruments businesses followed an unsolicited offer from the Cambridge, England-based maker of optical and scientific instruments.    Bausch andamp; Lomb said the businesses accounted for about $45 million, or 6%, of its $699 million in sales for 1986. The company said it didn't expect rapid growth in the businesses. </TEXT></DOC>